# Cost-Aware Agent Usage

- Prefer lower-cost models and agent types for exploration, planning, routine implementation, docs updates, and verification.
- Use expensive or high-reasoning models only when the task is genuinely complex, high-risk, security-sensitive, architecture-heavy, or blocked after cheaper attempts.
- Dispatch the fewest agents needed for the task. Use many agents only when parallel workstreams are clearly independent and valuable.
- Prefer readonly `explore` agents for codebase research before using heavier general-purpose agents.
- Keep each agent prompt tightly scoped so it returns actionable output without unnecessary token usage.
- Avoid repeating agent work that has already been completed in the current conversation.
